{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/weekNumberingYear"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week-numbering year in which the week containing","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"datetime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" falls."}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"title":"weekNumberingYear","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"weekNumberingYear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"}],"role":"symbol","extendedModule":"GLib","roleHeading":"Instance Property","externalID":"s:4GLib16DateTimeProtocolPAAE17weekNumberingYearSivp::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib8DateTimeC","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"property"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/datetime\/weeknumberingyear"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"weekNumberingYear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" { "},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function, taken together with "},{"code":"g_date_time_get_week_of_year()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_date_time_get_day_of_week()"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used to determine the full ISO"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"week date on which "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"datetime"},{"text":" falls.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is usually equal to the normal Gregorian year (as returned by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_date_time_get_year()"},{"type":"text","text":"), except as detailed below:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For Thursday, the week-numbering year is always equal to the usual"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"calendar year.  For other days, the number is such that every day","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"within a complete week (Monday to Sunday) is contained within the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"same week-numbering year."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday occurring near the end of the year,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this may mean that the week-numbering year is one greater than the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"calendar year (so that these days have the same week-numbering year","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as the Thursday occurring early in the next year)."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For Friday, Saturday and Sunday occurring near the start of the year,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this may mean that the week-numbering year is one less than the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calendar year (so that these days have the same week-numbering year"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as the Thursday occurring late in the previous year)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"An equivalent description is that the week-numbering year is equal to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the calendar year containing the majority of the days in the current"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"week (Monday to Sunday)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that January 1 0001 in the proleptic Gregorian calendar is a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Monday, so this function never returns 0."}]}]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTime":{"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DateTime","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DateTime"}],"title":"DateTime","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetime","abstract":[{"code":"GDateTime","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a structure that combines a Gregorian date and time","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"into a single structure.","type":"text"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTime/weekNumberingYear":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/weekNumberingYear","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"weekNumberingYear"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetime\/weeknumberingyear","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week-numbering year in which the week containing","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"datetime"},{"text":" falls.","type":"text"}],"title":"weekNumberingYear","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTime/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations":{"type":"topic","title":"DateTimeProtocol Implementations","kind":"article","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetime\/datetimeprotocol-implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib